.DS_Store

# The entire datasets/ directory is excluded from git (2026-07-20, second
# cleanup pass) - previously a handful of small metadata files (sampled_
# images.json, attack_metadata.json, and their DocLayNet/adversarial
# variants) were kept tracked deliberately, since they define exactly which
# images were sampled and which random attack parameters were chosen,
# letting a fresh clone reproduce the same experiment exactly. Excluding
# them too was an explicit user decision to keep GitHub minimal - the
# tradeoff: a fresh clone can still run the full download -> sample ->
# attack-generate pipeline and get a statistically equivalent dataset (same
# RANDOM_SEED, same HF dataset revision), but not a byte-identical one,
# since the frozen sample/attack choices themselves are no longer version-
# controlled. All of it remains present on disk locally, untouched.
datasets/

typographic/outputs/
*.pkl
*.egg-info/

adversarial/outputs/
